<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1267,1760]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName authority="Steindachner, 1892" authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1892" box="[151,641,1303,1328]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,641,1303,1328]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,387,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Dasyatis marmorata</emphasis>
(Steindachner, 
<number box="[576,633,1303,1328]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1892.0">1892</number>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was reported firstly in the Gulf of Gabes (south 
<collectingCountry box="[1215,1300,1303,1327]" name="Tunisia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Maurin" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Maurin, C. &amp; Bonnet, M. (1970) Poissons des cotes nord-ouest africaines (campagnes de la Thalassa) (1962 et 1968) Revue des Travaux de l'Institut scientifique et technique des Peches maritimes, 34, 125 - 170." type="journal article" year="1970">
Maurin and Bonnet (
<number box="[296,355,1340,1364]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1970.0">1970</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName box="[402,547,1341,1364]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pastinaca">
<emphasis box="[402,547,1341,1364]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D. pastinaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[554,730,1341,1364]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="variety" variety="marmorata">
var. 
<emphasis box="[604,730,1341,1364]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the presence of this taxon in south 
<collectingCountry box="[1142,1225,1340,1364]" name="Tunisia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
was confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Quignard" box="[151,481,1375,1399]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Quignard, J. P. &amp; Capape C. (1971) Liste commentee des selaciens de Tunisie. Bulletin de la Station d'Oceanographie et de Peche de Salammbo, 2 (2), 131 - 141." type="journal article" year="1971">
Quignard and Capapé (
<number box="[415,473,1375,1399]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1971.0">1971</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and included in the Mediterranean ichthyofauna by 
<bibRefCitation author="Quignard" box="[1079,1432,1375,1399]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Quignard, J. P. &amp; Tomasini, J. A. (2000) Mediterranean fish biodiversity. Biologia Marina Mediterranea, 7 (3), 1 - 66." type="journal article" year="2000">
Quignard and Tomasini (
<number box="[1362,1424,1375,1399]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2000.0">2000</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Later the species was considered as synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[713,874,1412,1436]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chrysonota">
<emphasis box="[713,874,1412,1436]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D. chrysonota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and recorded under this name in the eastern and central Mediterranean by 
<bibRefCitation author="Golani" box="[450,757,1447,1471]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Golani, D. &amp; Capape, C. (2004) First records of the blue stingray, Dasyatis chrysonota (Smith, 1828) (Chondrichthyes: Dasyatidae), off the coast of Israel. Acta Adriatica, 45, 107 - 112." type="journal article" year="2004">
Golani and Capapè (
<number box="[689,748,1447,1471]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[817,1085,1447,1472]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="El Kamel, O., Mnasri, N., Ben Souissi, J., Boumaiza, M., Ben Amor, M. M. &amp; Capape, C. (2009) Inventory of elasmobranch species caugth in the Lagoon of Bizerte (North-eastern Tunisia, central Mediterranean). Pan-American Journal of Aquatic Sciences, 4, 383 - 412." type="journal article">
El Kamel 
<emphasis box="[938,990,1448,1472]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[1016,1077,1447,1471]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2009.0">2009</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, respectively. However, in the upcoming volume dealing with batoid fishes of the Food and Agricolture Organisation Species Identification Field Guide for Fishery Purposes (Séret, in press), 
<taxonomicName box="[717,886,1521,1544]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[717,886,1521,1544]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered a species of West Africa and Mediterranean and 
<taxonomicName box="[372,532,1556,1580]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chrysonota">
<emphasis box="[372,532,1556,1580]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D. chrysonota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a South African species; nevertheless a genetic study is needed to reaffirm the validity of 
<taxonomicName box="[274,434,1593,1616]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[274,434,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and redefine the two species (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Bradai" box="[869,1081,1591,1616]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Bradai, M. N., Saidi, B. &amp; Enajjar, S. (2010) Elasmobranchs of the Mediterranean and Black Sea: Status, ecology and biology- Bibliographic analysis. General Fisheries Commission for theMediterranean. 151.1.154.86 / GfcmWebSite / GFCM / 35 / GFCM _ XXXV _ 2011 _ Dma. 3. pdf" type="journal article" year="2010">
Bradai 
<emphasis box="[951,1000,1592,1616]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number box="[1020,1081,1591,1615]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1267,1760]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName authority="Capape, 1975" authorityName="Capape" authorityYear="1975" box="[151,547,1627,1652]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tortonesei">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,547,1627,1652]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,373,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Dasyatis tortonesei</emphasis>
Capapé, 
<number box="[491,547,1627,1652]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1975.0">1975</number>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is considered dubious by 
<bibRefCitation author="Compagno" box="[859,1067,1628,1652]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Compagno, L. J. V. (1999) Checklist of living elasmobranchs. In: Hamlett, W. C. (Ed.), Sharks, Skates, and Rays. The biology of elasmobranch fishes. The Johns Hopkins University press, Baltimore, Maryland, pp. 471 - 498." type="book chapter" year="1999">
Compagno (
<number box="[1000,1058,1628,1652]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and excluded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Serena" box="[1275,1436,1628,1652]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Serena, F. (2005) Field identification guide to sharks and rays of the Mediterranean and Black Sea. FAO Species Identification Guide for Fishery Purposes. FAO, Rome, 97 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Serena (
<number box="[1369,1428,1628,1652]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
from the “Field identification guide to sharks and rays of the Mediterranean and Black Sea”. Morphometric and meristic data along with parasitological studies on individuals collected in the Gulf of Gabes, seem to indicate that 
<taxonomicName box="[151,297,1737,1760]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tortonesei">
<emphasis box="[151,297,1737,1760]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D. tortonesei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a valid species distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Bradai et al., 2010" authorityName="Bradai et al." authorityYear="2010" box="[718,1098,1735,1760]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pastinaca">
<emphasis box="[718,860,1737,1760]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D. pastinaca</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bradai" box="[875,1090,1735,1760]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Bradai, M. N., Saidi, B. &amp; Enajjar, S. (2010) Elasmobranchs of the Mediterranean and Black Sea: Status, ecology and biology- Bibliographic analysis. General Fisheries Commission for theMediterranean. 151.1.154.86 / GfcmWebSite / GFCM / 35 / GFCM _ XXXV _ 2011 _ Dma. 3. pdf" type="journal article" year="2010">
Bradai 
<emphasis box="[959,1008,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number box="[1029,1090,1735,1759]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
